bib_record.title: Level density and mechanism of deuteron-induced reactions on 54,56,58Fe

free_txt: Experiments were carried out at the
Edwards Accelerator Laboratory of Ohio University
using the 4.5 MV tandem accelerator
Experiments were carried out at the
Edwards Accelerator Laboratory of Ohio University
using the 4.5 MV tandem accelerator
Charged particle measurements were performed
using the charged particle spectrometer composed of a
target chamber with attached TOF tubes and silicon
surface barrier detectors. The detectors were
positioned such that they cover the angular range
from 37.5deg to 157.5deg. The flight path in the
forward directions was 2 m, whereas in the backward
directions, it was 1 m.
No uncertainties given
Self-supporting 54Fe foil with
thicknesses of 610 mu-g/cm2
Data presented in fig. 2 sent by author

The experimental nuclear level density is
extracted from experimental particle evaporation
spectrum using the Hauser-Feshbach model. Absolute
normalization was done by matching the experimental
data points to the calculated ones in the region of
known discrete low-lying levels
